handleBaseUri

protected void handleBaseUri(org.openrdf.rio.RDFWriter writer)
                      throws IOException,
                             org.openrdf.rio.RDFHandlerException
Handles the definition of the base URI during serialization. This method handles it by actually writing the base URI if one is defined.

Current implementation does nothing due to lack of underlying Sesame support.

Parameters:
writer - the writer to which the serialization is happening
Throws:
IOException - if the writer throws this exception
org.openrdf.rio.RDFHandlerException - if an internal error occurs
